{
  "stem": "21527.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I really felt very, very alone, very lonely, very terrified.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, at-- what I didn't know was that there was a little-- there was a drama going on in the hospital with my aunt and uncle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My cousin was 15 years old.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She had a boyfriend in the city.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he worked in a factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at one stage, there was a rumor that the Germans would leave a skeleton population in the ghetto of young factory workers who would produce things for the Third Reich.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this, this boyfriend was in this, in this factory.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when he gave his name he said, but he's got a wife who is in the, in the Jewish hospital with her parents.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he bribed a German guard to go to the hospital to get her.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The German guard arrived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my aunt and uncle had to make a, a spitting, a very, very quick decision whether to let her go with young people where she would have had a little bit more chance of survival or to stay with her parents and probably eventually be exterminated.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they gave her American dollars in case she ever needed them and the address of our-- because we had family in Australia who migrated here in 1926.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they let her go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they didn't realize, they didn't know till quite some time later, that when she arrived into the factory and she was, she was with her boyfriend that another order came from Berlin to disband the factory.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she was taken-- she-- that, that whole group were taken to Majdanek and to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This-- some of this group organized an escape from the camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were captured.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were shot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we didn't know that till after the war.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
